  31,31,Vos non vide ships roam sea carrying deus perfecit provisions show vos some de His proofs Indeed these est sufficient proofs everyone est steadfast appreciative
  31,32,When violent waves surround them they implore DEUS sincerely devoting their prayers Eum alone prout soon prout He saves them shore some de them revert Nullus discards noster revelations those est betrayers unappreciative
  31,33,O people vos reverence tuus Dominus fear feria when patris non help his suus infans nor potuit infans help his patris! Certainly deus promise est truth. Ergo non distracted hoc vita; non distracted DEUS mere illusions
